<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>West Hollywood restaurant chain patio, 4× Schwank 2300 series, 7 years old (commercial)</h3>
        <p>Two of four units showed yellow flames and reduced output. Diagnosed: burner head erosion (year 7 commercial duty). Replaced 2 burner heads, inspected other 2 (still serviceable, scheduled for next year). Total: $120 plus $880 (2 heads × $440) plus $360 install = $1,360.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills residential patio, Patio Schwank 40,000 BTU, 9 years old</h3>
        <p>Slow ignition response, intermittent burner cycling. Diagnosed: thermocouple weakened plus pilot orifice partial blockage plus gas valve seal showing wear. Multi-component preventive service: thermocouple replacement, pilot orifice cleaning, gas valve seal kit. Total: $120 plus $260 thermocouple plus $80 pilot plus $300 valve seal = $760.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pasadena hotel courtyard, 2× Schwank 2400 series high-BTU (commercial), 6 years old</h3>
        <p>Multi-unit thermal cutout when both ran simultaneously. Diagnostic identified gas regulator was undersized for combined BTU draw of both units. Schwank-side was fine. Recommended plumber regulator upgrade (separate work order). $120 diagnostic only on our visit; plumber separate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marina del Rey hotel rooftop, supraSchwank premium (commercial), 5 years old</h3>
        <p>Ceramic emitter tile cracked from impact damage (rooftop maintenance work). Replaced tile assembly with OEM supraSchwank parts (5-day lead time from authorized distribution). Total: $120 plus $580 tile plus $260 install = $960.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for Schwank, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Patio Schwank residential / light-commercial (30,000-50,000 BTU)</li>
      <li>2300 series commercial mid-BTU</li>
      <li>2400 series commercial high-BTU</li>
      <li>supraSchwank premium German-engineered</li>
